2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25338,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/25\/ibn-qayyim-reason-nature\/","url_meta":{"origin":22392,"position":1},"title":"Ibn Qayyim on Reason: Islam conforms to reason and nature","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 25, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Qayyim reported: It was said to one of the Bedouins who embraced Islam, when he recognized the call of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, \u201cWhat made you become a Muslim? What did you see in him that told you he is the Messenger of Allah?\u201d The\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":30912,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/24\/hasan-aql-kindness-half\/","url_meta":{"origin":22392,"position":2},"title":"Hasan on &#8216;Aql: Loving kindness is half of sound reason","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 24, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abi Dunya reported: Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \"Loving kindness towards people is half of reason.\" Source:\u00a0Muda\u0304ra\u0304t al-Na\u0304s 44 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u00a0\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0651\u064e\u0648\u064e\u062f\u0651\u064f\u062f\u064f \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u0650 \u0646\u0650\u0635\u0652\u0641\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0642\u0652\u0644\u0650 44 \u0645\u062f\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0627\u0633 \u0644\u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0628\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0646\u064a\u0627","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24910,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/05\/31\/discuss-islam-hereafter-masjid\/","url_meta":{"origin":22392,"position":3},"title":"Hasan on Mosques: Only discuss Islam in the Masjid","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 31, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Hazim reported: Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cA time will come to people when their discussions in the mosques will be about the affairs of their world. Allah has no need of it, so do not sit with them.\u201d Source: Mus\u0323annaf Ibn Abi\u0304 Shaybah 34622\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21680,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/01\/19\/ibn-jawzi-weak-mawdu-hadith\/","url_meta":{"origin":22392,"position":4},"title":"Ibn Jawzi on Hadith: How to recognize a Hadith is weak or fabricated","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 19, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Jawzi said, \u201cIf you find a prophetic narration disagreeing with sound reason, contradicting established revelation, or conflicting with the principles, know that it is inauthentic.\u201d Al-Suyuti said, \u201cThe meaning of conflicting with the principles is that it falls outside the literature of Islam, the transmitted sciences and the famous\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24386,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/02\/06\/kattani-deen-three-pillars\/","url_meta":{"origin":22392,"position":5},"title":"Kattani on Islam: Religion of Allah is truth, justice, and honesty","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 6, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Ghazali reported: Muhammad ibn Ali al-Kattani, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cWe have found that the religion of Allah Almighty is built upon three pillars: truth, honesty, and justice. Truth is in the body, justice is in the heart, and honesty is in the mind.\u201d Source: Ih\u0323ya\u0304\u2019 \u2018Ulu\u0304m\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/22392","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/user